td.content:
Tinea Unguium/onychomycosis: also known as onychomycosis, is a fungal infection of the nail. Symptoms may include white or yellow nail discoloration, thickening of the nail, and separation of the nail from the nail bed. As They thicken they can cause a pain and infection. Treatment includes oral medications, topicals and laser treatments. Topicals and lasers help, but unlikely to "cure" the problem. Oral medications work the best, but, are not guaranteed and have the possibility of affecting the Liver. Recommended treatment is topicals with frequent nail debridement and burring. Toe pain relieved with debridement
BUNION: A bunion is a bony bump that forms on the joint at the base of your big toe. It occurs when some of the bones in the front part of your foot move out of place. It is usually more of an angular deformity than a bump of bone. This causes your big toe to get pulled toward the smaller toes and forces the joint at the base of your big toe to stick out. The main cause of bunions is heredity, but, shoe gear and injury can also contribute.
Pain foot/ankle: Rest, Ice and elevation. Decrease activity and OTC meds as tolerated and needed,

Goal: Tinea Unguium/onychomycosis: also known as onychomycosis, is a fungal infection of the nail. Symptoms may include white or yellow nail discoloration, thickening of the nail, and separation of the nail from the nail bed. As They thicken they can cause a pain and infection. Treatment includes oral medications, topicals and laser treatments. Topicals and lasers help, but unlikely to "cure" the problem. Oral medications work the best, but, are not guaranteed and have the possibility of affecting the Liver. Recommended treatment is topicals with frequent nail debridement and burring.

BUNION: A bunion is a bony bump that forms on the joint at the base of your big toe. It occurs when some of the bones in the front part of your foot move out of place. It is usually more of an angular deformity than a bump of bone. This causes your big toe to get pulled toward the smaller toes and forces the joint at the base of your big toe to stick out. The main cause of bunions is heredity, but, shoe gear and injury can also contribute.
